Classical source texts (public domain):
《卜筮正宗》(Qing dynasty, Wang Hongxu) and 《增删卜易》(Qing dynasty,
Yehe Laoren / Li Wenhui). The bundled data/*.txt are verbatim public-domain
full texts extracted by ctext.org (中国哲学书电子化计划); source attributed
per ctext terms. Modern collated/annotated editions are NOT included.

Methodology (constitution): hexagram construction follows 《卜筮正宗》,
divination follows 《增删卜易》; shensha are excluded from core logic;
schools are not mixed.
